column12: DISPOSITIF DE RANGEMENT DISPOSE SUR UN PANNEAU INTERIEUR D’UN VEHICULE
column13: DISPOSITIF DE RANGEMENT DISPOSE SUR UN PANNEAU INTERIEUR D’UN VEHICULE La présente invention est prévue pour proposer un compartiment de rangement (100) disposé sur un panneau intérieur d’un véhicule. Le compartiment de rangement (100) comprend : - un boîtier (50) définissant un espace de rangement pour ranger des articles, - un couvercle (110) avec une patte pivotante (112) agencée de manière pivotante afin de déplacer le couvercle (110) autour d’un axe de pivot entre une position ouverte et une position fermée, - un élément de verrouillage agencé sur une périphérie externe (101) du boîtier (50), et - un élément de butée (130) faisant saillie de la patte pivotante (112) du couvercle (110) de sorte que l’élément de butée (130) est adapté pour venir en butée et se mettre en prise avec l’élément de verrouillage flexible (120) pour maintenir le couvercle (110) dans la position ouverte (100a). Figure pour l'abrégé : Figure 4

column12: A METHOD AND A DEVICE FOR OPERATING PEM FUEL CELL WITH CO CONTAMINATED HYDROGEN GAS
column13: An apparatus (108) for purifying impure hydrogen fuel is described that includes a first chamber (120) and a second chamber (122). The first chamber (120) is configured to receive impure hydrogen fuel in the form of a first mixture of gases with hydrogen gas and carbon monoxide at the first concentration while the second chamber (122) is configured to receive a second mixture of gases with hydrogen gas at the second concentration. The apparatus (108) also includes a solid-state electrolyte (124) that separates the first chamber (120) and the second chamber (122) and includes an adsorbing catalyst (124). The apparatus (108) also includes a pair of electrodes (126-1, 126-2) installed each in the first chamber (120) and the second chamber (122) to create a potential difference is created across the solid-state electrolyte (124).

column12: Method and apparatus for operating PEM fuel cell with CO-contaminated hydrogen
column13: An apparatus (108) for purifying an impure hydrogen fuel is described herein. The apparatus (108) includes a first chamber (120) and a second chamber (122). The first chamber (120) is configured to receive an impure hydrogen fuel in the form of a first gas mixture having carbon monoxide and hydrogen at a first concentration, and the second chamber (122) is configured to receive a second gas mixture having hydrogen at a second concentration. The device (108) also includes a solid electrolyte (124). The solid electrolyte (124) separates the first chamber (120) and the second chamber (122) and includes an adsorption catalyst (124). The device (108) further comprises a pair of electrodes (126-1, 126-2). And a pair of electrodes (126-1, 126-2) mounted in the first chamber (120) and the second chamber (122), respectively, to form a potential difference across the solid electrolyte (124).

column12: METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR OPERATING PEM FUEL CELL WITH CO-CONTAMINATED HYDROGEN GAS
column13: To remove carbon monoxide from supply of a non-pure hydrogen fuel with lower power consumption while holding an appropriate amount of hydrogen gas to a fuel cell.SOLUTION: An apparatus (108) for purifying a non-pure hydrogen fuel includes a first chamber (120) and a second chamber (122). The first chamber (120) receives the non-pure hydrogen fuel in a form of a first gas mixture containing hydrogen having first concentration and carbon monoxide. On the other hand, the second chamber (122) receives a second gas mixture containing hydrogen gas having second concentration. The apparatus (108) includes a solid electrolyte (124) for partitioning the first chamber (120) and the second chamber (122), and includes an adsorption catalyst (124). The apparatus (108) includes a pair of electrodes (126-1, 126-2) installed in each of the first chamber (120) and the second chamber (122), and generates a potential difference through a solid catalyst (124).SELECTED DRAWING: Figure 1

column12: CO A METHOD AND A DEVICE FOR OPERATING PEM FUEL CELL WITH CO CONTAMINATED HYDROGEN GAS
column13: The present invention relates to a device for operating a solid polymer fuel cell with a CO-contaminated hydrogen gas, which removes carbon dioxide from a hydrogen fuel, and a method thereof. According to the present invention, a device (108) for purifying impure hydrogen fuel comprises: a first chamber (120); a second chamber (122); a solid-state electrolyte (124) including an adsorption catalyst and separating the first chamber (120) and the second chamber (122); and a pair of electrodes (126-1, 126-2) installed within each of the first chamber (120) and the second chamber (122) to form a potential difference across the solid-state electrolyte (124). The first chamber (120) is configured to store impure hydrogen fuel in the form of a first mixed gas including a first concentration of carbon monoxide and hydrogen gas and the second chamber (122) is configured to store a second mixed gas including a second concentration of hydrogen gas.

column12: SINGLE STAGE PROCESS FOR PRODUCTION OF HYDROGEN ENRICHED GAS
column13: The present invention discloses a single stage energy efficient process for production of hydrogen enriched/mixed gas at low temperature. More particularly, the present invention discloses a single stage energy efficient process for production of hydrogen enriched compressed natural gas (CNG) or LPG or biogas at low temperature.
